ZH: 这堂课非常枯燥，让我困得难受。
EN: This class is so boring, it makes me feel sleepy.

ZH: 他的演讲实在太枯燥了，我差点就睡着了。
EN: His speech is really dull, I almost fell asleep.

ZH: 常规会议总是让人感到枯燥乏味。
EN: Regular meetings always feel monotonous.

ZH: 这本小说细节过多，显得有点枯燥。
EN: This novel is too detailed, it's a bit tedious.

ZH: 威廉姆教授的课一向令人枯燥无味。
EN: Professor Williams' lectures are always dry and uninteresting.

ZH: 长时间看电视可能会导致生活过于枯燥。
EN: Watching TV for a long time may lead to a monotonous life.

ZH: 常常做同样的工作会使生活变得枯燥乏味。
EN: Doing the same job repeatedly can make life dull.

ZH: 这部电影的故事情节实在太枯燥了。
EN: The plot of this movie is just too boring.

ZH: 无聊的工作使她觉得整个生活都是枯燥的。
EN: The boring job makes her feel like her whole life is monotonous.

ZH: 这个话题讨论得太多了，听起来有点枯燥了。
EN: This topic has been discussed too much, it sounds a bit dull.

ZH: 学校里的某些科目真的很枯燥。
EN: Some subjects in school are really boring.

ZH: 西部一带的地形比较平坦，显得有点枯燥。
EN: The terrain in the western region is relatively flat, making it seem dull.

ZH: 在周末无所事事是很枯燥的。
EN: It's boring to do nothing on weekends.

ZH: 他的生活很枯燥，每天都做着相同的事情。
EN: His life is monotonous, doing the same things every day.

ZH: 长时间的讲座很容易让人感到心烦意乱和枯燥。
EN: Long lectures can easily make people feel bored and dull.

ZH: 读这种书简直就是枯燥至极。
EN: Reading this kind of book is extremely dull.

ZH: 过节时会有些枯燥，因为没有特别的活动。
EN: Festivals can be a bit dull, because there are no special activities.

ZH: 我们需要找点儿有意思的事做，这样不会觉得枯燥。
EN: We need to find something interesting to do so we won't feel bored.

ZH: 小时候，我在乏味的课堂里感到很枯燥。
EN: When I was a child, I felt very bored in dull classes.

ZH: 连续一个星期的练习课让我感到了很枯燥。
EN: A week of continuous practice classes made me feel very dull.
